  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "Determining the \"most underrated\" romantic movie can be subjective, as different audiences appreciate various aspects of romance films. However, one film that frequently surfaces in discussions about underrated romantic movies is **\"About Time\" (2013)**.\n\n### **About Time (2013)**\n\n**Directed by:** Richard Curtis  \n**Starring:** Domhnall Gleeson, Rachel McAdams, Bill Nighy\n\n#### **Why It's Considered Underrated:**\n\n1. **Unique Take on Romance and Time Travel:**\n   - Unlike typical romantic films, \"About Time\" incorporates time travel as a central element, allowing the protagonist to revisit and alter moments in his life. This adds depth to the exploration of love, relationships, and personal growth.\n\n2. **Emotional Depth:**\n   - The movie delves into profound themes such as family, loss, and the importance of cherishing everyday moments. Its heartfelt narrative resonates deeply with many viewers, offering more than just a surface-level romance story.\n\n3. **Strong Performances:**\n   - Domhnall Gleeson delivers a sincere performance as Tim, while Rachel McAdams brings warmth and authenticity to her role as Mary. The supporting cast, including Bill Nighy as Tim's father, adds richness to the story.\n\n4. **Balanced Tone:**\n   - \"About Time\" masterfully balances humor and emotion, creating a film that is both uplifting and poignant. Its ability to evoke laughter and tears without feeling manipulative is a testament to its thoughtful storytelling.\n\n5. **Message about Life and Love:**\n   - The film emphasizes living in the moment and appreciating the simple joys of life and love. This universal message resonates with many, making it a meaningful watch that lingers long after the credits roll.\n\n### **Other Noteworthy Underrated Romantic Films:**\n\nWhile \"About Time\" stands out, here are a few other romantic movies that many consider underrated:\n\n- **\"The Adjustment Bureau\" (2011):**\n  - A blend of romance and sci-fi, exploring fate and free will in relationships.\n\n- **\"Begin Again\" (2013):**\n  - Focuses on love, music, and second chances, with standout performances by Keira Knightley and Mark Ruffalo.\n\n- **\"Safety Not Guaranteed\" (2012):**\n  - Combines romance with a quirky time-travel premise, offering a fresh take on the genre.\n\n- **\"The Spectacular Now\" (2013):**\n  - A coming-of-age romance that delves into personal struggles and the complexities of young love.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\n\"About Time\" is often celebrated for its heartfelt storytelling and unique premise, making it a strong contender for one of the most underrated romantic movies. However, the beauty of romance films lies in their diversity, and exploring different titles can uncover numerous gems that resonate personally with each viewer.",
